cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on dropout training for convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of dropout in deep learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new technique called probabilistic weighted pooling, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper compares max-pooling dropout and stochastic pooling, which is relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
